text: John Booth (born 29 July 1942) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League (VFL). He later played with Port Melbourne and Brunswick in the Victorian Football Association (VFA). == Notes == == External links == * * Category:Living people Category:1942 births Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Essendon Football Club players Category:Fitzroy Football Club players Category:Doutta Stars Football Club players Category:Port Melbourne Football Club players Category:Brunswick Football Club players
